						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Vīraveṅkaṭarāya. Year <hi rend="italic">Śārvari, Vaikāśi</hi> 20, 1600-01 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. This inscription is very carelessly engraved. It seems that during the headship <hi rend="italic">(pārāpattiyam)</hi> of a certain Tāttāchāriya some gift was made to the Aḻagiyasiṅga (shrine) of Tirunīrmalai. Other details are not clear.</p>						

